      <h2>Understanding Gaming Mouse Categories</h2>
      <h3>FPS (First-Person Shooter)</h3>
      <p>FPS mice prioritize low weight, flawless sensors, and minimal button clutter. The goal is to allow for fast, precise flick shots and effortless tracking. Typical weights are under 60 grams.</p>

      <h3>MOBA & MMO (Multiplayer Online Battle Arena / Massively Multiplayer Online)</h3>
      <p>These mice focus on providing numerous accessible buttons for binding abilities, macros, and items. MMO mice often feature a 12-button side panel, while MOBA mice might offer a 6-button hex layout.</p>

      <h3>Wireless vs. Wired</h3>
      <p>Wireless technology has advanced to the point where 2.4GHz dongles provide latency on par with wired connections. The main considerations are now battery life, weight (due to the internal battery), and convenience.</p>

      <h3>Ergonomic vs. Ambidextrous</h3>
      <p>Ergonomic mice are shaped to fit the natural curve of a specific hand (usually right). Ambidextrous mice are symmetrical, suitable for both left and right-handed users, and often preferred by claw and fingertip grip users.</p>
